volumeInfo.title: Marvel Comics Presents Willow
volumeInfo.subtitle: The Illustrated Version
volumeInfo.description: A child, born with a mark on her arm -- the mark, according to an age-old prophecy, of the one who will bring down Queen Bavmorda -- becomes the evil Queen's greatest fear and Willow Ufgood, the magician, the child's only hope.

volumeInfo.title: The Battle for Argon Falls
volumeInfo.description: Pastor James and Brittany gather her friends to pray for Hana, a San Francisco schoolgirl who faces grave danger in the final battle with Urn'Ado that will determine the fate of the parallel world of Argon Falls.

volumeInfo.title: Elfquest
volumeInfo.subtitle: The Final Quest
volumeInfo.description: "The Palace of the High Ones is changing the elves. Cutter's daughter Ember and her tribe must fight of the tyrant Angrif Djun"--

volumeInfo.title: My Little Pony: Adventures in Friendship
volumeInfo.description: Rainbow Dash takes on a very stubborn cloud, Fluttershy faces her fear of criticism, and Rainbow Dash helps Trixie escape a big problem.

volumeInfo.title: Avatar: the Last Airbender--North and South Part Three
volumeInfo.description: "Created by Bryan Konietzko, Michael Dante DiMartino"--Preliminaries.

volumeInfo.title: Out from Boneville
volumeInfo.description: The adventure starts when cousins Fone Bone, Phoney Bone, and Smiley Bone are run out of Boneville and later get separated and lost in the wilderness, meeting monsters and making friends as they attempt to return home.

volumeInfo.title: Wingman
volumeInfo.description: To escape the problems of being poor and Chinese, Donald begins to cut school to climb the George Washington Bridge where he meets Wingman, a sort of Chinese Superman.

volumeInfo.title: ElfQuest Archives
volumeInfo.description: Presents the first five issues of the original comic, ElfQuest, with its wolfriders, trolls and supertstitious human beings trying to coexist on the World of Two Moons.

volumeInfo.title: Traveler
volumeInfo.description: After lonely college student Keiichi dials a wrong number, his wish of having a goddess as a companion is granted, and many adventures ensue involving him, his goddess girlfriend, her older sister, and other unworldly friends.

volumeInfo.title: Ninja Master
volumeInfo.description: Oh My Goddess!

volumeInfo.title: Oh My Goddess!
volumeInfo.subtitle: Miss Keiichi
volumeInfo.description: After lonely college student Keiichi dials a wrong number, his wish of having a goddess as a companion is granted, and many adventures ensue involving him, his goddess girlfriend, her older sister, and other unworldly friends.

volumeInfo.title: The Cry from Beyond
volumeInfo.description: Grade level: 8, 9, 10, 11, 12, i, s.

volumeInfo.title: Sea of Storms
volumeInfo.description: When a terrifying new threat emerges from the black abyss miles below the surface of the ocean, Aquaman must defeat the creatures of the trench in order to save humanity.

volumeInfo.title: Viminy Crowe's Comic Book
volumeInfo.description: When Wylder Wallace spills his lunch on Addy Crowe at ComicFest then discovers that her uncle is a steampunk comic artist, Wylder embarks on a series of adventures with Addy involving the loss of her pet rat and the unfolding of a comic book story.

volumeInfo.title: Hilda and the Black Hound
volumeInfo.description: In Hilda's new adventure, she meets the Nisse - a mischievous but charismatic bunch of misfits with some intriguing secrets.

volumeInfo.title: Wonder Woman
volumeInfo.subtitle: Challenge of the Gods
volumeInfo.description: Follows the adventures of Wonder Woman who faces many adversaries, including the Greek god Ares and the Olympian god Hermes.

volumeInfo.title: Quest's End
volumeInfo.description: Cutter and his Wolfriders have escaped the prison of Blue Mountain, but, as they journey towards the Palace of the High Ones, the ancient home to all elves, they are set upon by the inimical and bellicose trolls. Cutter and his band are forced to nurse their wounds in the lodges of the Go-Backs and each wonders whom, if any one, will survive the First and Final War?

volumeInfo.title: Death note
volumeInfo.subtitle: Give-and-take
volumeInfo.description: When high school student Light Yagami finds the Death Note, a notebook dropped by a Shinigami death god, he discovers that any person whose name is written in it dies, so Light decides to use the notebook to rid the world of evil.

volumeInfo.title: Siege at Blue Mountain
volumeInfo.description: The Wolfriders have settled into their new Holt in the Forbidden Grove. The tumult of the Quest is behind them, and new life has come to the tribe. All is peaceful until a Wolfrider child is kidnapped. The elves must once again confront Winnowill and her schemes -- but first they must get through the humans who worship the evil temptress!

volumeInfo.title: The Argon Deception
volumeInfo.description: As prophesied, Hana, a schoolgirl in San Francisco, returns to the parallel world of Argon Falls, accompanied by Grandfather Jou and the shape-shifting, talking raccoon, Tomo, to prepare to battle an enemy who wants to enslave the kingdom by first obtaining Hana's sword of the Spirit.

volumeInfo.title: New Blood
volumeInfo.subtitle: Original Visions of Elfquest
volumeInfo.description: The Wolfriders, a band of elves, search for others of their kind in a savage Earthlike world.

volumeInfo.title: Wolfrider
volumeInfo.description: Graphic novel. Cutter's father Bearclaw was the tenth chief of the Wolfriders, and his reign was marked by frequent skirmishes with humans.

volumeInfo.title: Transmetropolitan
volumeInfo.subtitle: Tales of Human Waste
volumeInfo.description: From an award-winning author, this final book features excerpts from the "Word" columns of crazed outlaw journalist Spider Jerusalem. Suggested for mature readers. Full color.

volumeInfo.title: Fire and Flight
volumeInfo.description: Fire and flight is the first adventure of the forest dwelling Wolfriders. Vengeful humans have destroyed the elves' ancestral home after having conspired with the cowardly trolls. Cutter, the elves' leader, directs his elfin fellows across the Burning Wastelands to find a new home. Can the elfin tribe survive? If they do, what storehouse of surprises awaits them at Sorrow's End?

volumeInfo.title: Powerless
volumeInfo.description: "Contains material originally published in magazine form as Powerless #1-6."

volumeInfo.title: Rogue's Challenge
volumeInfo.description: Rayek searches for a way to restore his powers and regain the confidence of his fellow elves.

volumeInfo.title: The Secret of Two-Edge
volumeInfo.description: Within the corridors of Blue Mountain, Winnowill has hatched her most ambitious plan ever -- to take her people away from the World of Two Moons and back to the stars. To accomplish this, she must be rid of the Wolfriders. As her human slaves and Cutter's tribe fights for its survival. Winnowill prepares her final, mind-boggling assault.

volumeInfo.title: Child of Destiny
volumeInfo.description: Hana learns how her coming into Argon Falls fulfills a prophecy, and Tomo tells Hana about her past, her parents, and the mysterious stranger responsible for the warfare in this other dimension.

volumeInfo.title: Chikyu Misaki
volumeInfo.description: After inheriting her grandfather's house in a small village, Misaki meets Neo, an odd shape-shifting creature who looks like a small Loch Ness Monster, and she finds it hard to keep his existence--which is a local legend--a secret.

volumeInfo.title: Save Yourself
volumeInfo.description: When she becomes locked in a tower along with her sisters, Princess Adrienne recruits her pet dragon, Sparky, to help her save herself rather than wait for a prince to rescue her.

volumeInfo.title: Captives of Blue Mountain
volumeInfo.description: The Wolfriders are taken as slaves into the mysterious Blue Mountain, the stronghold of the ancient Glider elves, while Cutter and Skywise try to come to their rescue.

volumeInfo.title: Adventure Time: Sugary Shorts
volumeInfo.description: Collects the adventures of such Land of Ooo residents as Finn the Human, Jake the Dog, Princess Bubblegum, and Marceline the Vampire Queen.

volumeInfo.title: Flight Explorer
volumeInfo.description: Collects imaginative comic strips and short stories in graphic novel format.

volumeInfo.title: NFL Rush Zone: Season of the Guardians 1
volumeInfo.subtitle: San Francisco 49ers: Variant Edition
volumeInfo.description: Ish, the first NFL Guardian, is charged with protecting the NFL Powercores from a mysterious, otherworldly threat.

volumeInfo.title: Truth Revealed
volumeInfo.description: The tie between Argon Falls and San Francisco becomes even stronger as Tomo and Hana learn new secrets, and Jou is taken prisoner by the evil King Ardath.

volumeInfo.title: Secret Alliance
volumeInfo.description: When Tomo and Hana pursue deadly assassins who have returned to Earth to destroy the power of prayer, they learn that not all warriors fight with fists and swords.

volumeInfo.title: Adventure Time
volumeInfo.description: After a battle with the Ice King and saving the princess, Finn and Jake discover a series of dungeons ready for exploring.

volumeInfo.title: Wolverine/Punisher
volumeInfo.description: Marvel's bad boys of the big screen join forces for a gun-toting, claw-popping adventure not to be forgotten! Deep in the South American jungle there's a place of legend - a final refuge where nastiest of the masty can disappear from the prying eyes of the world. Now, the vigilante known as the Punisher and the X-Man called Wolverine have stumbled upon this secret sanctuary, and the residents of "Erewhon" couldn't be happier...or more prepared. Collects WOLVERINE/PUNISHER #1-5.

volumeInfo.title: Bone
volumeInfo.subtitle: The great cow race. Vol. 2
volumeInfo.description: Before leaving the village of Barrelhaven, Phoney Bone risks everything on one last get-rich-quick scheme for the town's annual Great Cow Race, but as usual, Phoney's plans go disastrously awry. Tween.

volumeInfo.title: My Little Pony Legends Of Magic
volumeInfo.description: It?s all here- the origins of cutie marks, friendships, magic, and more! In this opening story arc, we travel back in time to uncover the secrets of Starswirl the Bearded and his magical friends! Sure to entice longtime readers, it also makes a good entry point for new fans of the characters.

volumeInfo.title: North and South
volumeInfo.description: "Created by Bryan Konietzko, Michael Dante DiMartino"--Preliminaries.

volumeInfo.title: Hook
volumeInfo.subtitle: The Official Movie Adaptation
volumeInfo.description: Using a cartoon format, portrays Peter Pan as an adult searching for his children after they are kidnapped from the nursery by the dreaded Captain Hook.

volumeInfo.title: Blood of Ten Chiefs
volumeInfo.description: Stories from the dark and wild past of the wolfrider tribe and the chiefs that led up to Cutter's time.

volumeInfo.title: Dungeon: The Early Years
volumeInfo.subtitle: Vol. 1 - The Night Shirt
volumeInfo.description: In the first story of the Early Years of the vast world of Dungeon, the Keeper--barely Mature--leaves his family to go find fortune in a time of chaos and darkness. Original.

volumeInfo.title: Wolverine Classic
volumeInfo.description: He's known by many names: Logan, Weapon X, Wolverine. One fact is certain: He's the best there is at what he does, and what he does isn't pretty! Here - in stories collected for the first time in color - the feral X-Man adopts his now-infamous "Patch" identity in Madripoor as he tries to track down the mystical Black Sword of legend. Featuring Jessica Drew, a.k.a. Spider-Woman, and Silver Samurai! Plus: General Coy moves into Madripoor, sending his new goons after rival crimelord Tyger Tiger. Can Wolverine and his allies keep the peace? Collects Wolverine (1988) #1-5.

volumeInfo.title: Monkey King
volumeInfo.subtitle: The stolen kingdom. Vol. 09
volumeInfo.description: As they continue their journey to the west, San Zang and his disciples are sought out by a vengeful ghost to help right an injustice involving a stolen kingdom.

volumeInfo.title: Avatar: the Last Airbender - the Rift Library Edition
volumeInfo.description: When Avatar Aang and his friends embark on a journey to honor an Air Nomad holiday, a cryptic visit from the spirit of Avatar Yangchen leads Aang to a refinery operating on sacred land, and soon everyone is in peril from a dangerous ancient spirit.

volumeInfo.title: Mae
volumeInfo.description: "This volume collects the Dark Horse Comics series Mae #1-#6"

volumeInfo.title: Arkham Asylum
volumeInfo.subtitle: A Serious House on Serious Earth
volumeInfo.description: Led by the Joker, the inmates have taken over Arkham Asylum, Gotham's mental illness detention center, and are holding the staff hostage. Their demands are many, but one stands out: they want Batman in there with them. Batman takes their challenge to save the hostages, but risks losing his own sanity in the process. Includes the annoted script for the comic and original page layouts.

volumeInfo.title: The Legend of the Fire Princess (She-Ra Graphic Novel #1)
volumeInfo.description: Don't miss the first epic She-Ra and the Princesses of Power graphic novel, based on stories by showrunner Noelle Stevenson! Even after everything that's happened, the world outside the Horde's walls is still a strange one to Adora. Each day she's learning more about her growing powers as She-Ra, including something new: the ability to heal corrupted runestones. Runestones are the magical source from which princesses like Frosta, Mermista, and Perfuma draw their power, but Glimmer knows of another runestone -- one with a dark past. Long ago a fire princess ruled the lands to the west, until her thirst for power corrupted her, and led to the ruin of her kingdom. Glimmer thinks the lost fire runestone could give the Rebellion an edge in the fight against the Horde, but claiming this ancient power won't be easy... especially not when the Horde has their eyes set on the same prize. Don't miss this original graphic novel based on stories by She-Ra showrunner and New York Times bestselling author Noelle Stevenson, with script by Gigi D.G. and art by Paulina Ganucheau!

volumeInfo.title: Secret Skull
volumeInfo.description: Steve Niles's "Meeednight Pulps" debuts with this story of girls, guns, and ghouls! A mysterious killer is on the loose in the city, but this killer only kills bad guys... or those about to be bad. Do the police bring him in - or leave him to ply his deadly trade?

volumeInfo.title: The Far-Out Fairies
volumeInfo.description: Three stories about fairies-in-training Ivy, Holly, and Fern, that are designed to be read phonetically by beginning readers. Presented in comic-book format.

volumeInfo.title: Amulet
volumeInfo.subtitle: The cloud searchers. Book three
volumeInfo.description: A latest entry in the best-selling series finds Emily, Navin and the gang traveling by airship in search of the mythical cloud city of Cielis, a quest that is joined by the dubiously trustworthy son of the Elf King. Original.

volumeInfo.title: Aliens Predator, Deadliest of the Species
volumeInfo.description: The second part of a science-fiction saga of multinational intrigue, illegal slave-trading and interstellar travel. Caryn Delacroix, wife of corporate mogul Lucien, is unable to tell what is real and what is virtual when she comes face to face with the Predator in the jungles of Earth.

volumeInfo.title: Fantastic Cinema Subject Guide
volumeInfo.subtitle: A Topical Index to 2500 Horror, Science Fiction, and Fantasy Films
volumeInfo.description: About 2,500 genre films are entered under more than 100 subject headings, ranging from abominable snowmen through dreamkillers, rats, and time travel, to zombies, with a brief essay on each topic: development, highlights, and trends. Each film entry shows year of release, distribution company, country of origin, director, producer, screenwriter, cinematographer, cast credits, plot synopsis and critical commentary.

volumeInfo.title: Knights of Madness
volumeInfo.subtitle: Further Comic Tales of Fantasy
volumeInfo.description: When comedy enters the world of fantasy, anything can happen - and it usually does in the inventive hands of such brilliant writers as Terry Pratchett, Tom Sharpe and Spike Milligan, all of whom are featured in this uproarious new collection. Following on from the spectacular success of THE WIZARDS OF ODD and THE FLYING SORCERERS, KNIGHTS OF MADNESS presents fantasy at its most comic in a collection of SF, heroic romance and crime. With Terry Pratchett creating mayhem on the Hollywood freeway and Peter S. Beagle running riot with a New Yorker who just happens to be a werewolf; with manic knights, crazed astronauts and bungling criminals, here are stories that rollick from hilarity to absurdity, from satire to the bizarre, in a glorious melange of wit and imaginative genius.

volumeInfo.title: Nausicaä of the Valley of Wind
Batman
volumeInfo.subtitle: As the Crow Flies
volumeInfo.description: Batman tries to restore order in Gotham City after the Penguin and the Scarecrow begin a murderous rampage.

volumeInfo.title: Time Guardian
volumeInfo.description: When high school student Miu Asahina stumbles upon a shop where time is loaned to anybody who needs it for the price of a memory, Miu decides to work there and help other people manage their time.

volumeInfo.title: Pieces of a Spiral
volumeInfo.description: When Sakuya and Wakyo, two reincarnated souls from feudal Japan, learn that their mentor, Bishu, is in grave danger from their archenemy, they set out to rescue him from the demons at work.

volumeInfo.title: Fire
volumeInfo.description: "It was a day like any other for Dara Brighton, a promising young college student, until three powerful strangers knocked on her door, looking for a mysteriously powerful sword. During their search, they brutally murdered her family and destroyed her life. But Dara's journey has just begun"--P. [4] of cover.

volumeInfo.title: Tenryu
volumeInfo.subtitle: The Dragon Cycle
volumeInfo.description: When two brothers seek to avenge their father's death in war-town ancient China, they stumble upon the secrets of their origin while meeting up with plenty of weapon-wielding women and foes only too happy to end their quest.

volumeInfo.title: The Remarkable Worlds of Professor Phineas B. Fuddle
volumeInfo.description: After his uncle, Professor Fuddle, creates a time machine to bring technology to ancient peoples and accidentally starts the destruction of the universe, McKee and his friend Angus must follow Fuddle back into the past and stop him.

volumeInfo.title: Tenryu the Dragon Cycle
volumeInfo.description: When two brothers seek to avenge their father's death in war-town ancient China, they stumble upon the secrets of their origin while meeting up with plenty of weapon-wielding women and foes only too happy to end their quest.

volumeInfo.title: King of Cards
volumeInfo.description: Chronicles the adventures of a schoolgirl named Manami and other players in a trading card game named "Chaos," where the line between real life and fantasy is blurred, and the stakes of the game have significant consequences for everyone involved.

volumeInfo.title: Courageous Princess, the Volume 1 Beyond the Hundred Kingdoms (3rd Edition)
volumeInfo.description: When the beloved Princess Mabelrose is kidnapped by a dragon, she decides that, instead of waiting to be rescued, she will use her intelligence and courage to make her own way home, with a little help from new friends made along the way.

volumeInfo.title: Myth Adventures!
volumeInfo.description: "Skeeve is an apprentice magician, Aahz is a 'demon' summoned by Skeeve's master. Now the master magician is dead, Aahz has lost his magic, and somebody out there is responsible for the whole mess. While Aahz tries to find out who, Skeeve must dodge assassins, con artists, demon hunters and an overly affectionate dragon ; all while trying to learn enough magic to save the world without embarassing himself in the process"--Page 4 of cover.

volumeInfo.title: Pieces of a Spiral
volumeInfo.description: When Sakuya and Wakyo, two reincarnated souls from feudal Japan, learn that their mentor, Bishu, is in grave danger from their archenemy, they set out to rescue him from the demons at work.

volumeInfo.title: Neil Gaiman and Charles Vess's Stardust
volumeInfo.subtitle: Being a Romance Within the Realms of Faerie
volumeInfo.description: In the sleepy English countryside of decades past, a lovelorn young man steps through a gap in a high stone wall, and into the most unforgettable adventure of his life.

volumeInfo.title: Seimaden
volumeInfo.description: The demon king, Laures, and Roddrick, a teenager, are blinded by their love for the same woman, Hilda, as they deal with betrayal by their most trusted friends and attempts by the villain Tetius to destroy them both.

volumeInfo.title: Death
volumeInfo.description: Collects all of Gaiman's tales starring Death, including her first appearance in the "Sandman" series and a story in which, as a young mortal girl named Didi, she helps a 250-year-old homeless woman find her missing heart.

volumeInfo.title: Justice League Unlimited
volumeInfo.subtitle: United They Stand
volumeInfo.description: Superman, Batman, Wonder Woman, and the rest of the Justice League battle a collection of intergalactic villains.

volumeInfo.title: Deep Sleeper Trade Paperback
volumeInfo.description: Cole Gibson is haunted by vivid and terrifying nightmares that cripple his career and alienate his family. He soon discovers his dreams are merely doorways into a separate, hidden level of reality populated by beings beyond imagining. The menacing forces lurking in this realm crave one prize above all -- Cole Gibson's soul.

volumeInfo.title: Adventure Time Original Graphic Novel Vol. 1: Playing With Fire
volumeInfo.description: Includes: Adventure time with BMO! / written and illustrated by Meredith McClaren.

volumeInfo.title: The Maze
volumeInfo.publisher: Random House Books for Young Readers
volumeInfo.description: When three teenagers, each with their own personal problems, set out for the Lost City on the island of Dinotopia, they discover an alien breed of dinosaurs and gain insights into themselves as well.

volumeInfo.title: Anna & Elsa #4: The Great Ice Engine (Disney Frozen)
volumeInfo.description: A new chapter book series featuring the stars of Disney's Frozen finds Elsa using her magical powers over ice and snow, and Anna following her own adventurous, loving spirit to explore their home and kingdom. Movie tie-in.

volumeInfo.title: Pete Von Sholly's Morbid
volumeInfo.description: A parody of low-budget horror movies uses illustrations, photographs, and exclamation points to mock terrifying tales.

volumeInfo.title: Anna & Elsa #9: Princess in Charge (Disney Frozen)
volumeInfo.description: When Elsa has to leave Arendelle for a day, Anna is left in charge! Princess Anna, Queen Elsa, Olaf the snowman, and all the characters from Disney Frozen star in this magical chapter-book series perfect for newly independent readers ages 6 to 9.

volumeInfo.title: Havoc
volumeInfo.description: Having escaped from the comic book world of Malice alone, Seth must decide whether to remain there, or return to Malice, where his best friend Kady is trapped and plotting to overthow Tall Jake with the help of a rebel group called Havoc.

volumeInfo.title: Leave it to Chance
volumeInfo.description: "[T]he adventure of a lifetime, filled with shape shifting Trogs, Indian mysticism, Sewer Goblins, a fire breathing dragon, and even a monstrous sized, city destroying Toad... Leave it to Chance is guaranteed to charm readers of all ages" -- notes.

volumeInfo.title: Green Lantern Legacy
volumeInfo.subtitle: The Last Will & Testament of Hal Jordan
volumeInfo.description: When the Justice League of America and former Green Lanterns want Hal Jordan forgotten, Tom and Hal's son Marty must figure out how to fulfill his final request.

volumeInfo.title: Tellos Colossal
volumeInfo.description: "Tellos is a magikal patchwork world made up of a myriad of different realms, populated by Creatures of Myth and Legend, a fantastic land filled with adventure around every corner and danger at every turn" -- back cover.

volumeInfo.title: My Neighbor Totoro
volumeInfo.description: Mei, a four-year-old girl, and her older sister, Satsuki, move with their father to an old house in the country, where the girls meet a group of magical creatures called totoros, which can not be seen by adults.

volumeInfo.title: Adventure Time Vol. 3 Mathematical Edition
volumeInfo.description: If they ever want to play video games again, Finn, Jake, and Marceline must figure out how to fix BMO, which has been given a virus by an evil wizard.

volumeInfo.title: Dorothy and the Wizard in Oz
volumeInfo.description: During a California earthquake Dorothy falls into the underground Land of the Mangaboos where she again meets the Wizard of Oz.

volumeInfo.title: New Alice in Wonderland
volumeInfo.description: Manga adaptation of the story of a girl who follows a talking rabbit down a hole and discovers a world of nonsensical and amusing characters.

volumeInfo.title: Dystopia
volumeInfo.subtitle: Post-Apocalyptic Art, Fiction and the Movies
volumeInfo.description: We have an obsession with broken societies set in futuristic worlds, curious but terrifying new technologies and post-apocalyptic dusty wastelands where survivors grow more desperate every day. Dystopian themes are becoming ever more popular and this is the book to show the art, fiction and movies.

volumeInfo.title: Eyes of the Storm
volumeInfo.description: The adventure starts when cousins Fone Bone, Phoney Bone, and Smiley Bone are run out of Boneville and later get separated and lost in the wilderness, meeting monsters and making friends as they attempt to return home.

volumeInfo.title: Curses! Foiled Again
volumeInfo.description: Follows New York City high school fencer Aliera Carstair's continuing adventures as the defender of the Seelie realm.

volumeInfo.title: Megaman Nt Warrior 8
volumeInfo.description: Fifth-grader Lan Hikari and MegaMan unite to thwart the sinister organization World Three's quest to take over the world.

volumeInfo.title: The Smurfs Graphic Novels Boxed Set: Vol. #10-12
volumeInfo.description: Collects Smurf adventures in which Smurfette returns to the village with an announcement, the Smurfs compete in the first Olympic games, and the Smurfs are divided over which Smurf language is correct.

volumeInfo.title: Betty and Veronica Storybook
volumeInfo.description: Betty, Veronica, and the rest of the Riverdale crew star in versions of famous fairy tales and fantasy stories, including "Sleeping Beauty" and "Alice in Wonderland."

volumeInfo.title: Fantastic Four
volumeInfo.subtitle: The Ultimate Guide
volumeInfo.description: Exposed to intense radioactive rays during a voyage into space, four friends; Reed richards, Ben Grimm, Sue Storm and her brother Johnny - would never be the same again. Each member of the ill-fated crew was genetically altered by the rays developed a unique superhuman power.

volumeInfo.title: The Cycle of Air
volumeInfo.description: Okko, a samurai without a master, and his three companions, a giant, a monk, and a young fisherman, encounter such adversaries as bandits, vampires, puppets, demons, and samurai thugs as they wander through the Pajan Empire, where the great clans are fighting for control.

volumeInfo.title: Gulliver's Travels
volumeInfo.description: In graphic novel format, retells Swift's tale of an eighteenth-century Englishman shipwrecked on the island of Lilliput, where the people are six inches tall.

volumeInfo.title: Death Note 5
volumeInfo.subtitle: Whiteout
volumeInfo.description: When high school student Light Yagami finds the Death Note, a notebook dropped by a Shinigami death god, he discovers that any person whose name is written in it dies, so Light decides to use the notebook to rid the world of evil.

volumeInfo.title: Adventure Time Original Graphic Novel Vol. 5: Graybles Schmaybles
volumeInfo.description: After waking up in the treehouse, Finn and Jake find a little purple cube that is able to activate a watchable screen, a strange situation that leads to adventure.

volumeInfo.title: Death Note 12
volumeInfo.description: When high school student Light Yagami finds the Death Note, a notebook dropped by a Shinigami death god, he discovers that any person whose name is written in it dies, so Light decides to use the notebook to rid the world of evil.

volumeInfo.title: Antiquitas Lost
volumeInfo.subtitle: The Last of the Shamalans
volumeInfo.description: Deformed teenager Elliott Orion stumbles through a doorway in his grandfather's basement into the war-torn world of Pangrelor, where he meets gargoyles, wizards, and neanderthals, and embarks on a quest to save its greatest civilization.

volumeInfo.title: Death Note 7
volumeInfo.description: When high school student Light Yagami finds the Death Note, a notebook dropped by a Shinigami death god, he discovers that any person whose name is written in it dies, so Light decides to use the notebook to rid the world of evil.

volumeInfo.title: Tenryu
volumeInfo.subtitle: The Dragon Cycle
volumeInfo.description: When two brothers seek to avenge their father's death in war-town ancient China, they stumble upon the secrets of their origin while meeting up with plenty of weapon-wielding women and foes only too happy to end their quest.

volumeInfo.title: Batman's Top Secret Tools
volumeInfo.subtitle: A Guide to the Gadgets
volumeInfo.description: "Gotham City is overrun by villains of all shapes and sizes. It’s up to Batman and his allies to stop them, but they can’t do it without the help of some high-tech gear! Head into the Batcave to get a glimpse at all of the spectacular vehicles and tools Batman and his allies use to save the day!"--Publisher.

volumeInfo.title: Unwanted
volumeInfo.description: All her life, Bea has wanted nothing more than to become a sniper on the wall and earn the coveted ink of a Dread warrior - a mark of distinction among her people. She knows that one day the terrifying Erebii might break through the city's outer defences, and if her people aren't prepared and the wall is breached then the last human city will fall. But everything Bea thinks she knows is about to be challenged... What does the ink really do as it flows underneath their skin and who is the mysterious Unwanted boy that keeps appearing in her life?

volumeInfo.title: The Invincible Ed
volumeInfo.description: Ed, mistakenly receiving the alien power of invincibility, learns to be a hero through self-sacrifice and confidence.

volumeInfo.title: Scarygirl
volumeInfo.description: After being dumped on a remote beach in a pile of trash, Scarygirl sets out, with the help of a super-intelligent giant octopus named Blister, to find out the truth about her past and the man who haunts her dreams.

volumeInfo.title: Broxo
volumeInfo.description: "Broxo, the only surviving member of a tribe of barbarians, spends his time on a mountain hunting and avoiding the man-eating walking dead until everything changes when Zora, a foreign princess, arrives on the mountain seeking Broxo's lost tribe"--

volumeInfo.title: Elfquest Bedtime Stories
volumeInfo.subtitle: New Old Favorite Tales
volumeInfo.description: Retelling of familiar fairy tales in an Elfquest setting.

volumeInfo.title: Animal Land 9
volumeInfo.description: When they tackle the Tower of Babel and its chimera guards, Taroza and his friends unexpectedly encounter humans, and Taroza's leadership skills are tested when he is forced to choose between the group's goal and his friends' lives.

volumeInfo.title: Krishna
volumeInfo.subtitle: Defender of Dharma
volumeInfo.description: Krishna, the eighth avatar of Lord Vishnu, embarks on a journey to vanquish the evil on Earth, from monsters, demons, and ogres to the greedy and arrogant kings, princes, and warriors to restore peace and dharma.

volumeInfo.title: Animal Land
volumeInfo.description: When Monoko finds a human baby that can communicate with the animals, he decides to team up with the baby to protect the tanuki pack from vicious wildcats.

volumeInfo.title: Deltora Quest 9
volumeInfo.description: The exciting adventure continues in Deltora Quest 9, the manga adaptation of the beloved Deltora Quest series. The series follows Lief, who has set out to complete his father's quest to save Deltora from the Shadow Lord. Joining Lief is an ex-palace guard Barda and wild child Jasmine, who can speak to trees. Their quest is to find the seven gems of the fabled Belt of Deltora so they can defeat the Shadow Lord and allow the one sole heir to take their rightful place on the throne.

volumeInfo.title: Diversity Alliance
volumeInfo.description: When a fellow Jedi student, who holds the key to a New Republic secret coalition, turns up missing, the young Jedi Knights race across the galaxy to find him and are forced to confront a deadly enemy.

volumeInfo.title: Spider-Man
volumeInfo.subtitle: India
volumeInfo.description: A "what if" story that places Spider-Man in India instead of New York. Pavitr Prabhakar is a teenager from a small village who moves to Mumbai (Bombay) for a better education. The story describes how he becomes Spider-Man, witnesses the death of his Uncle Bhim, and must fight two demonic villains for the lives of his girlfriend Meera Jain and his Aunt Maya.

volumeInfo.title: The Marvelous Land of Oz
volumeInfo.description: Join new characters Tip and Jack Pumpkinhead as they're whisked to Oz, and meet foes and friends! You've NEVER seen L. Frank Baum's masterpiece like this before

volumeInfo.title: Stray Little Devil
volumeInfo.description: While trying to summon a devil with her friends, thirteen-year-old Pam is surprised when she is transported to an alternate world in which she has become a little devil--and if she wants to get back home, she must become a full-fledged one.

volumeInfo.title: Gulliver's Travels
volumeInfo.description: A graphic novel adaptation of the tale of the voyages of an Englishman that carry him to such strange places as Lilliput, where people are six inches tall; Brobdingnag, a land of giants; and a country ruled by horses.

volumeInfo.title: Dragon Arms
volumeInfo.subtitle: Blood and Steel Pocket Manga
volumeInfo.description: When the heroes of the past have become corrupt tyrannical leaders, five new heroes, assembled by the ancient wizard Anrack, are instructed in the use of Dragon Arms, powerful weapons, to overthrow the leaders and establish peace.

volumeInfo.title: The Last Airbender
volumeInfo.subtitle: Prequel : Zuko's Story
volumeInfo.description: Zuko, prince of the Fire Nation, is banished and scarred by his father for questioning his authority, and must learn to harness his firebending power and battle his inner demons while on a quest to capture the long-lost Avatar.
